benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: Valid Request: The tests cover successful resume flows (TC01) and variations with parameters (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC18).
Non-Existing Resource: 404 when attempting to resume a non-existent bundle (TC05).

Authorization & Input Validation: Tests cover missing header (TC07) and invalid token (TC10); invalid bundleId format (TC06); invalid pluginProperty/input formats (TC19); past/future date handling (TC20).
State & Concurrency: Tests cover invalid state transitions (active/cancelled) (TC08, TC09) and concurrent requests (TC21).
Error Handling & Resilience: 500 for dependency service downtime (TC14); retry scenario (TC15); 504 possibility in plugin service timeout (TC25).
Security: SQL injection attempt in pluginProperty (TC16); XSS attempt in X-Killbill-Comment header (TC17).
Edge & Boundary Cases: Max header lengths (TC12); whitespace/case variations in headers (TC26); large pluginProperty payloads (TC13).
Regression & Compatibility: Regression case (TC23); backward compatibility with legacy headers (TC24).
Audit Logging: Reason and comment are recorded in the audit log (TC04).
Partial Update: Partial input with only required fields is supported (TC18) and combined optional parameters (TC04).
Large Payload Handling: 1000 pluginProperty values tested (TC13).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests validating throttling or burst handling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control).
Partial Update Rejection: No explicit test for rejecting partial updates if not allowed (current tests imply support for partial input).
Duplicate Submission/Idempotency: No explicit idempotency/duplicate-submission tests.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests for PUT /resume to validate behavior under burst traffic.
Add tests around caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching behavior.
Add explicit test to verify rejection of partial updates if the API should not allow them (or adjust tests if partial updates are allowed).
Add idempotency/duplicate-submission tests to ensure repeated requests behave predictably.
